# register/ is versioned on purpose — git diff over register/ is how Saul tracks corpus drift.
# Do not ignore it.

# The law corpus is 114 MB and re-clonable from legalize-ch; keep it out of git EXCEPT the
# vendored seed (four complete codes), so a fresh clone of THIS repo answers everyday questions
# offline. Run ./launch.sh to fetch the rest; it is never committed here. corpus/ch/ is flat, so
# ignoring its direct children (corpus/ch/*) lets the seed negations below re-include the four files.
corpus/ch/*
!corpus/ch/.gitkeep
# vendored seed (.gitignore has no inline comments, so keep these on their own lines):
# cc-1999-404 = BV (SR 101), cc-27-317_321_377 = OR (220), cc-54-757_781_799 = StGB-AT (311.0), cc-2022-491 = DSG (235.1)
!corpus/ch/cc-1999-404.md
!corpus/ch/cc-27-317_321_377.md
!corpus/ch/cc-54-757_781_799.md
!corpus/ch/cc-2022-491.md

# OS / tooling cruft.
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Never commit a stray secret even if one slips into the tree.
*.env
.env
*.pem
*.key
*_secret*
